==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Colly
<hw>Col"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Coal</er>.]</ety> <def>The black grime or soot of coal.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Burton.</au></rj></p>

<p><ent>Colly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Colly
<hw>Col"ly</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Collied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Collying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To render black or dark, as of
with coal smut; to begrime.</def> <mark>[Archaic.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou hast not <qex>collied</qex> thy face enough.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Brief as the lighting in the <qex>collied</qex> night.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Colly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Colly
<hw>Col"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of dog. See
<er>Collie</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

